First Lady Michelle Obama is involved in several upcoming events and initiatives. She recently released a music video with Jay Pharoah as part of the #BetterMakeRoom campaign. She also issued a surprise challenge for young designers on Project Runway: Junior in collaboration with Lands' End as part of the Let Girls Learn initiative. Additionally, she had an interview with the Financial Times. 

In terms of upcoming guidance, on Monday, December 14, 2015, Mrs. Obama will be visiting the Children's National Health System in Washington, DC. She will tour the hospital, visit patients, and thank the staff for their work. She will also read to children and take their questions in the hospital's atrium. 

On Friday, December 18, 2015, as part of the Joining Forces initiative, the First Lady will greet children of Gold Star families attending a special screening of Star Wars: The Force Awakens in the White House Family Theater.